import * as React from 'react'; : This imports the entire react module and assigns it to the React variable. 
        The * is a wildcard that means to import everything from the module.

{ View, Text, StyleSheet }: This uses destructuring to import the View, Text, and StyleSheet components from the react-native module.

React.Component: is a base class for React components, and defines a set of methods and properties that are common to all components.
When you define a new component, you typically extend React.Component to inherit its functionality.

{ View, Text, StyleSheet }: This uses destructuring to import the View, Text, and StyleSheet components from the react-native module.

View, Text, and StyleSheet are components provided by the react-native library. View is a container that provides a way to structure and group components, 
Text is used for displaying text, and StyleSheet is used for styling components.

eg 
here we use A or any thing mostly use React
import A from 'react';
import MyComponent from './MyComponent';

class App extends A.Component {
  render() {
    return (
      <div>
        <MyComponent />
      </div>
    );
  }
}

export default App;
